T1  - The Endogenous Determination of Time Preference*
PY  - 1997
Y1  - 1997/08/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355397555334
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 112
IS  - 3
SP  - 729
EP  - 758
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - We model a consumer's efforts to reduce the discount on future utilities. Our analysis shows how wealth, mortality, addictions, uncertainty, and other variables affect the degree of time preference. In addition to working out many implications of the model, we discuss evidence on consumption, savings, equilibrium, and the dynamics of inequality. We claim that most ofthat evidence is consistent with the predictions of our approach.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355397555334
ER  - 



