T1  - Unemployment Insurance Takeup Rates and the After-Tax Value of Benefits*
PY  - 1997
Y1  - 1997/08/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355397555389
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 112
IS  - 3
SP  - 913
EP  - 937
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - The recent decline in the unemployment insurance (UI) takeup rate has puzzled researchers. Using administrative data with accurate information on the potential level and duration of benefits, we examine whether a separating employee receives UI. We find a strong positive effect of the benefit level on takeup, and smaller effects of the potential duration and the tax treatment of benefits. Simulations indicate that the recent inclusion of UI in the income tax base can account for most of the previously unexplained decline in UI receipt.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355397555389
ER  - 



